INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (472001, 'Our sympathy is cold to the relation of distant misery.', 7427, 0), (472002, 'I sometimes get that wonderful sympathy between me and the audience, telling me I''ve reached their hearts. And when I do, the thrill is mine.', 73223, 0), (472003, 'Something that''s seldom appreciated about me is that I am in sympathy with a great deal of what Marx wrote, except that I''m on the side of the bourgeoisie.', 16098, 0), (472004, 'In order that people who suffer from depression seek treatment without a second thought, the stigmas must further fall until we reach a point in time when that person with leukemia and that person with depression both receive the same level of sympathy and the same level of rigorous treatment. Both people deserve it.', 150, 0), (472005, 'You will find that the woman who is really kind to dogs is always one who has failed to inspire sympathy in men.', 17074, 0), (472006, 'Recognition of belligerency as an expression of sympathy is all very well.', 65173, 0), (472007, 'Motherhood is at its best when the tender chords of sympathy have been touched.', 67906, 0), (472008, 'The humanitarian lays stress almost solely upon breadth of knowledge and sympathy.', 71965, 0), (472009, 'The true humanist maintains a just balance between sympathy and selection.', 71965, 0), (472010, 'I have a theory because I was being beaten up a lot by people outside of school, it was almost like if I could make myself sick enough they''d take sympathy on me.', 52956, 0), (472011, 'Those who weep recover more quickly than those who smile.', 42142, 0), (472012, 'As a Scot, I instinctively feel a sympathy towards a culture which is based on generosity. It''s very refreshing. Afghans think they''re the best people in the world and their country is the best place in the world, and it''s strange because you go there and it doesn''t really look like it, and yet they assume that everybody else envies them.', 17562, 0), (472013, 'Sympathy is charming, but it does not make up for pain.', 5328, 0), (472014, 'You have to have sympathy for and an empathy with a character in order to play them.', 67154, 0), (472015, 'Whether rich people make money or lose money, they get no sympathy from the public.', 72947, 0), (472016, 'We all have to announce our full solidarity with the struggle of those seeking freedom and justice in Syria, and translate this sympathy into a clear political vision that supports a peaceful transition to a democratic system of rule that reflects the demands of the Syrian people for freedom.', 74325, 0), (472017, 'This sympathy is not translated into force against the British government because it is not like the anti- apartheid movement which had a high profile here and Mandela is a more engaging figure than Yasser Arafat.', 74326, 0), (472018, 'The novelist must look on humanity without partiality or prejudice. His sympathy, like that of the historian, must be unbounded, and untainted by sect or party.', 62734, 0), (472019, 'It''s important to find characters that share sympathy with a young audience, not just in the story but their role in the world.', 73016, 0), (472020, 'The late Tom Wicker''s biography of Nixon, called ''One of Us,'' is really quite good: you see the biographer discovering dimensions of sympathy for his subject that he hadn''t expected to feel.', 5480, 0), (472021, 'I''m in total sympathy with Dick Smith''s sentiments I only wish there were grounds for saying we Australians would never tolerate such appalling treatment of refugees being carried out in our name. ', 73329, 0), (472022, 'I joined the Party definitely in 1923 after having already been in sympathy with it before.', 67174, 0), (472023, 'Sympathy is something that shouldn''t be bestowed upon the Yankees. Apparently it angers them.', 20783, 0), (472024, 'Criticism in the universities, I''ll have to admit, has entered a phase where I am totally out of sympathy with 95% of what goes on. It''s Stalinism without Stalin.', 4514, 0), (472025, 'I have a lot of sympathy for young people because I realize how disturbed I was. How would I deal with life in the future? What would I do for a living?', 69955, 0), (472026, 'According to your sympathy, you will take pleasure in your own happiness or in the happiness of other people; but it is always your own happiness you seek.', 74327, 0), (472027, 'Sonia Gandhi and her husband have always been persons I look at with a lot of respect. Of course, one of the reasons we look at India with a lot of sympathy and enthusiasm is Sonia Gandhi. Now she is Indian, not Italian, but she will always represent a myth for Italians.', 67922, 0), (472028, 'When men are arrested without any legal basis and for political reasons, it''s merely a routine, everyday occurrence in Russia, and hardly anyone has any sympathy.', 73384, 0), (472029, 'There''s no greater way to gain an audience''s sympathy than by being unfortunate.', 74328, 0), (472030, 'I don''t care about sympathy. I care about playing a character who''s understandable and clear.', 74329, 0), (472031, 'I don''t really distinguish between sympathy and honesty when I''m writing. The two go together - I''m interested in inhabiting my characters, seeing the world through their eyes.', 12043, 0), (472032, 'I have always thought it a great privilege to have as my colleague in the Palit Chair of Chemistry such a distinguished pioneer in scientific research and education in Bengal as Sir Prafulla Ray. It has been invariably my experience that I could count on his cooperation and sympathy in every matter concerning my scientific work.', 70901, 0), (472033, 'My mother listened to all the news from the camp during the strike. She said little, especially when my father or the men who worked for him were about I remember her instinctive and unhesitating sympathy for the miners.', 71205, 0), (472034, 'In the eyes of the Catholic Church, abortion is a tragedy. Our principle objective must be to try and win greater sympathy for that perspective and for the value of human life from its beginnings.', 69075, 0), (472035, 'But what you could perhaps do with in these days is a word of most sincere sympathy. Your movement is carried internally by so strong a truth and necessity that victory in one form or another cannot elude you for long.', 73930, 0), (472036, 'I believe that everyone can appreciate the right of a family to grieve the loss of a loved one in peace, regardless of anyone''s position on the war in Iraq and Afghanistan.', 73573, 0), (472037, 'You have to take strength from the people that love you and the people that love Barbara and the huge number of expressions of sympathy and compassion and support. That has been extremely moving.', 71971, 0), (472038, 'Actors who are lovers in real life are often incapable if playing the part of lovers to an audience. It is equally true that sympathy between actors who are not lovers may create a temporary emotion that is perfectly sincere.', 74330, 0), (472039, 'The easiest way for readers to connect with characters and feel sympathy is to make the character entertaining, sympathetic and likeable.', 7172, 0), (472040, 'Any relations in a social order will endure, if there is infused into them some of that spirit of human sympathy which qualifies life for immortality.', 66713, 0), (472041, 'Sympathy for victims is always counter-balanced by an equal and opposite feeling of resentment towards them.', 2234, 0), (472042, 'There should be a sympathy with freedom, a desire to give it scope, founded not upon visionary ideas, but upon the long experience of many generations within the shores of this happy isle, that in freedom you lay the firmest foundations both of loyalty and order.', 62935, 0), (472043, 'As Christians, our compassion is simply a response to the love that God has already shown us.', 31701, 0), (472044, 'There''s something very beautiful and compelling about someone who has ambition and someone who knows what they want, but it can get a little frustrating at times, so I understand that. I have sympathy for that.', 72306, 0), (472045, 'Although I''m Australian, I find myself much more in sympathy with the Austrian version!', 70583, 0), (472046, 'A creative element is surely present in all great systems, and it does not seem possible that all sympathy or fundamental attitudes of will can be entirely eliminated from any human philosophy.', 67228, 0), (472047, 'This is not a country that has had a tremendous sympathy for poor people, so I think that the notion that somehow we have slipped into an era in which poor people don''t matter is not quite the way our history would define it.', 16711, 0), (472048, 'It is by a wise economy of nature that those who suffer without change, and whom no one can help, become uninteresting. Yet so it may happen that those who need sympathy the most often attract it the least.', 10650, 0), (472049, 'I am the son of a small and far-away nation and the other laureates have all come from different countries from all over the world and we all were equally received here with signs of sympathy.', 13394, 0), (472050, 'Since this war began our sympathy has gone out to all the suffering people who have been dragged into it. Further hundreds of millions have become involved since I spoke at Limerick fortnight ago.', 67600, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (472051, 'If you want to devote yourself to the arts, you''d better do it strictly from passion, because there is zero guarantee that you''ll get anywhere. The hardest thing is dealing with business people who have nothing to do with your art. They could care less that you''re up at 4:30 in the morning writing a joke. Don''t expect any sympathy from anybody.', 68415, 0), (472052, 'Extremist perspectives win sympathy and recruits because they offer narratives that claim to identify deep injustices and enemies.', 74163, 0), (472053, 'In Shakespeare, unique individuals repudiate the stereotypes demanded by the structure of the play: Shylock commands our sympathy, Barnardine refuses to be hanged. Individuals trump the category.', 69873, 0), (472054, 'My guitar was loud as hell, and I had no sympathy for anybody else.', 74331, 0), (472055, 'Because I select my players from a feeling that comes to me when I am with them, a certain sympathy you might call it, or a vibration that exists between us that convinces me they are right.', 74332, 0), (472056, 'I have great sympathy for people that are infertile, but a life is not something you can give away.', 74333, 0), (472057, 'A crowd always thinks with its sympathy, never with its reason.', 72987, 0), (472058, 'The truth is that at the White House and in Congress, you are as likely to find sympathy for animal issues among Republicans as among Democrats.', 21179, 0), (472059, 'To the factory farmer, in contrast to the traditional farmer with his sense of honor and obligation, the animals are ''production units,'' and accorded all the sympathy that term suggests.', 21179, 0), (472060, 'California must be all American or all Chinese. We are resolved that it shall be American, and are prepared to make it so. May we not rely upon your sympathy and assistance?', 74334, 0), (472061, 'I don''t think it''s an incredibly radical premise to try and have sympathy for someone who has made a mistake.', 74335, 0), (472062, 'Okay, so, sometimes in life, I can be a score-keeper - someone who keeps track of what he gives and what he gets in return. An annoying quality, to say the least, and I''m sure my wife has your sympathy, but it''s made me highly attuned to when and where credit is due.', 74336, 0), (472063, 'If I''m feeling outraged, grief, disbelief, frustration, sympathy, that gets channeled through me and into my pictures and hopefully transmitted to the viewer.', 67710, 0), (472064, 'I think we lost a great deal of sympathy and support with the way in which the crisis was handled, most importantly I think when we appeared to be grasping for too much at one time instead of identifying our priorities in a much more responsible fashion.', 73504, 0), (472065, 'It''s hard for me to think of others because I''m not particularly in sympathy with the music of this century.', 70848, 0), (472066, 'Reasoned arguments and suggestions which make allowance for the full difficulties of the state of war that exists may help, and will always be listened to with respect and sympathy.', 74337, 0), (472067, 'The professional must learn to be moved and touched emotionally, yet at the same time stand back objectively: I''ve seen a lot of damage done by tea and sympathy.', 2795, 0), (472068, 'IT is mere coincidence that Cooper was born in the year which produced The Power of Sympathy and that when he died Uncle Tom''s Cabin was passing through its serial stage, and yet the limits of his life mark almost exactly the first great period of American fiction.', 25490, 0), (472069, 'In any business, the more you learn, the more sympathetic you can be to other people''s positions.', 74338, 0), (472070, 'Many of the artists who have represented Negro life have seen only the comic, ludicrous side of it, and have lacked sympathy with and appreciation for the warm big heart that dwells within such a rough exterior.', 73363, 0), (472071, 'More negatives write than call. It''s a cheap shot for me to go on the air with the critical letters or E-mail I get because the reaction of the listeners is always an instantaneous expression of sympathy for me and contempt for the poor critic.', 74339, 0), (472072, 'I have a lot of sympathy with the ideas and frustration of the Occupy movement. I absolutely agree with the sense that Wall Street has brought an economic calamity to the middle class and that no one has been held accountable.', 74340, 0), (472073, 'Kindliness and sympathy, fellowship and understanding, are always good, but best when they come from a distant corner of the world.', 73528, 0), (472074, 'Grief is only the memory of widowed affections.', 2916, 0), (472075, 'He bit his lip in a manner which immediately awakened my maternal sympathy, and I helped him bite it.', 13424, 0), (472076, 'All art is an intensely vulnerable gesture, and it is made with no small amounts of risk, and fear. So, I have plenty of sympathy for self-defense mechanisms, especially among artists.', 1562, 0), (472077, 'Queen Paola and I will never forget the ties that have grown between the people and us during the course of the years. Thank you for your confidence, tokens of sympathy and support, sometimes even with a little criticism. We always loved you.', 72442, 0), (472078, 'Grief is a normal and natural response to loss. It is originally an unlearned feeling process. Keeping grief inside increases your pain.', 74341, 0), (472079, 'I didn''t feel any remorse or sympathy if I injured a rival. I went over the top a few times but I never broke anyone''s leg.', 74342, 0), (472080, 'Poetry is partly sympathy, don''t you think? If it''s any good, it gets people to think about others'' points of view.', 901, 0), (472081, 'Sympathy with nature is part of a good person''s religion.', 70207, 0), (472082, 'I''m completely indifferent to what genre I read provided that I feel sympathy with how a writer perceives being alive in the world.', 2875, 0), (472083, 'Unfair discrimination exists whether we like it or not; I wouldn''t have married a gum-chewing vegetarian. Ultimately, we''ll help the people we discriminate against if we try to understand more about them; genetics will lead to a world where there is a sympathy for the underdog.', 60550, 0), (472084, 'Captain Hale, alone, without sympathy or support, save that from above, on the near approach of death asked for a clergyman to attend him. It was refused. He then requested a Bible; that too was refused by his inhuman jailer.', 74343, 0), (472085, 'I have the greatest sympathy with the growth of the socialist party. I think they understand the evils that surround us and hammer them into people''s minds better than we Liberals.', 74344, 0), (472086, 'Gratitude can transform common days into thanksgivings, turn routine jobs into joy, and change ordinary opportunities into blessings.', 1820, 0), (472087, 'Some memories are unforgettable, remaining ever vivid and heartwarming!', 4294, 0), (472088, 'Thanksgiving is one of my favorite days of the year because it reminds us to give thanks and to count our blessings. Suddenly, so many things become so little when we realize how blessed and lucky we are.', 69028, 0), (472089, 'I am grateful for what I am and have. My thanksgiving is perpetual.', 1049, 0), (472090, 'Gratitude is the inward feeling of kindness received. Thankfulness is the natural impulse to express that feeling. Thanksgiving is the following of that impulse.', 672, 0), (472091, 'You may have heard of Black Friday and Cyber Monday. There''s another day you might want to know about: Giving Tuesday. The idea is pretty straightforward. On the Tuesday after Thanksgiving, shoppers take a break from their gift-buying and donate what they can to charity.', 1133, 0), (472092, 'To give thanks in solitude is enough. Thanksgiving has wings and goes where it must go. Your prayer knows much more about it than you do.', 98, 0), (472093, 'Over and over I marvel at the blessings of my life: Each year has grown better than the last.', 13165, 0), (472094, 'I think that is a better thing than thanksgiving: thanks-living. How is this to be done? By a general cheerfulness of manner, by an obedience to the command of Him by whose mercy we live, by a perpetual, constant delighting of ourselves in the Lord, and by a submission of our desires to His will.', 36532, 0), (472095, 'Pride slays thanksgiving, but a humble mind is the soil out of which thanks naturally grow. A proud man is seldom a grateful man, for he never thinks he gets as much as he deserves.', 2175, 0), (472096, 'We''re getting ready to sit down at the table and have Thanksgiving, and there''s people that are not with their families. There are people that are in dangerous areas, putting their lives on the line to keep our country free, and I think that''s something we should all celebrate every day.', 69247, 0), (472097, 'My cooking is so bad my kids thought Thanksgiving was to commemorate Pearl Harbor.', 2181, 0), (472098, 'There is one day that is ours. Thanksgiving Day is the one day that is purely American.', 15417, 0), (472099, 'What a marvelous resource soup is for the thrifty cook - it solves the ham-bone and lamb-bone problems, the everlasting Thanksgiving turkey, the extra vegetables.', 1537, 0), (472100, 'Thanksgiving is America''s favorite holiday because it''s a time when we put aside our cares, much as the struggling Pilgrims did nearly four centuries ago, and eat a gut-busting meal without worrying about the ''out years.''', 60069, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (472101, 'Dear Lord; we beg but one boon more: Peace in the hearts of all men living, peace in the whole world this Thanksgiving.', 74345, 0), (472102, 'I give thanks to my Creator for this wonderful life where each of us has the opportunity to learn lessons we could not fully comprehend by any other means.', 4294, 0), (472103, 'What I love about Thanksgiving is that it''s purely about getting together with friends or family and enjoying food. It''s really for everybody, and it doesn''t matter where you''re from.', 69682, 0), (472104, 'I''ve seen terrorism close up, but I don''t live in a state of terror at all. I''m comfortable going to the Manhattan Thanksgiving Day Parade, the tree lighting at Rockefeller Center, Times Square on New Years Eve. For perspective, the world today is a safer place than it was during the Cuban Missile Crisis, the Berlin Airlift, World War II.', 59480, 0), (472105, 'Thanksgiving just gets me all warm and tingly and all kinds of wonderful inside.', 26513, 0), (472106, 'It is now common knowledge that the average American gains 7 pounds between Thanksgiving and New Year''s Day.', 66921, 0), (472107, 'That''s one of the great things about Thanksgiving: Football''s on!', 59728, 0), (472108, 'I''m not a big turkey fan, but my husband loves it. Thanksgiving is his favorite meal.', 1073, 0), (472109, 'My parents came from little, so they made a choice to give a lot: buying turkeys for homeless shelters at Thanksgiving, delivering meals to people in hospices, giving spare change to those asking for it.', 69330, 0), (472110, 'Thanksgiving was always a favorite holiday for me. The preparation was fun! My grandma and I would walk to the butcher on Jamaica Avenue in Queens, order the bird, and buy all the fixings at the market.', 66987, 0), (472111, 'My mother loved entertaining, and I''ve followed suit, so we have big celebrations for New Year, Passover, Thanksgiving and birthdays.', 17330, 0), (472112, 'I was introduced to the Turducken in New Orleans. And it wasn''t Thanksgiving. Glenn at the Gourmet Butcher Block brought it by, and I had never heard of it or had seen one, and they put it in the booth, and it smelled so good that I had to taste it. And it was good. Then Thanksgiving came, and we got one in addition to the traditional turkey.', 13024, 0), (472113, 'As governor, when I visited our troops in Kuwait and Iraq, I served them Thanksgiving dinner. It was a small gesture compared to their sacrifice.', 67870, 0), (472114, 'One of the best parts of Thanksgiving for me is re-watching some of the classic holiday blunders that have been depicted on television. I remember laughing uncontrollably on the set of ''That Girl'' back in 1967 when we shot the episode, ''Thanksgiving Comes But Once A Year, Hopefully'' during our second season.', 34804, 0), (472115, 'Let''s say you go to a friend''s wedding, or Thanksgiving, or Halloween. It''d be great the next day to see what went on with your friends'' Thanksgiving weekend, or all the costumes they wore on Halloween, and be able to look back and see what they wore the year before, and the year before that.', 74346, 0), (472116, 'Something I didn''t even know was on my bucket list has been achieved. I have cooked Thanksgiving dinner with Martha Stewart. I vow to follow the gospel of her teachings and do my very best in the remarkably less glamorous kitchen of my own home... without the luxury of magically appearing prep bowls filled by a staff of sous chefs.', 67524, 0), (472117, 'On Thanksgiving Night, 1942, when I was fifteen years old, white racists burned our house to the ground.', 16899, 0), (472118, 'Since 1981, I''ve spent every Thanksgiving Day broadcasting a game, and it is one of my favorite days. You can say, ''Woe is me, I never get to be part of the tradition,'' or you can say, ''Heck, we''ve got our own tradition, and it''s pretty good.''', 13024, 0), (472119, 'The more I come to recognize my story''s place in God''s grander Story, my once-bewildered questions are turning to psalms of thanksgiving at the wonder that I have been included in what He is doing.', 1558, 0), (472120, 'Shopmas now begins on Thanksgiving Day. Apparently, escaping the families you cannot stand to spend another minute with on Thanksgiving Day to go buy them gifts is how some Americans show their affection for one another. Weird.', 68893, 0), (472121, 'Thanksgiving is a season that is very much in accord with the themes and teachings of Jesus Christ.', 70238, 0), (472122, 'When people come to my act any time after Thanksgiving, I usually say, You shouldn''t be here. You should be shopping. Our economy depends on you! You should be out there buying stuff.''', 1870, 0), (472123, 'Christians were instructed to serve others, and the thanksgiving was for the grace of God and the fact that God offered a way for man to return to a positive relationship with Him.', 70238, 0), (472124, 'My mom makes something called green pie, which I thought was a delicacy that many people only had at Thanksgiving, but it turns out it was just Jell-O with whipped cream on it. And it''s delicious.', 73236, 0), (472125, 'I miss both of my parents terribly every day, but especially as we approach Thanksgiving. We always came together as a family for that holiday, playing capture the flag and touch football and laughing a lot.', 74347, 0), (472126, 'Halloween is fun, but it wasn''t always my favorite holiday. I think Thanksgiving is my favorite holiday.', 74348, 0), (472127, 'Where I grew up, I could be a punk rocker and a jock. But in college, it became apparent that those two worlds didn''t mix. When I brought my guitar back to school after Thanksgiving break, a friend handed me his bass and said, ''Listen to the Ramones.''', 74137, 0), (472128, 'It''s like being at the kids'' table at Thanksgiving - you can put your elbows on it, you don''t have to talk politics... no matter how old I get, there''s always a part of me that''s sitting there.', 55317, 0), (472129, 'There are three things that people pick up on the instant they walk into your home on Thanksgiving. They will be able to feel the human energy. They''ll smell the food. And they will see, instantly, the table.', 66636, 0), (472130, 'Being an Ethiopian-born, Swedish-raised chef, there''s nothing traditional about my Thanksgiving spread.', 32425, 0), (472131, 'I think Thanksgiving is the perfect occasion to break open a buttery, oaky Chardonnay from California.', 49967, 0), (472132, 'It''s a bit of a sore spot, the Thanksgiving in Indian country.', 68267, 0), (472133, 'Even if you are vegetarian, you do want to have a stuffing for Thanksgiving. The stuffing is not so much about the vegetables, but it''s very unique to the season.', 69682, 0), (472134, 'My favorite meal is turkey and mashed potatoes. I love Thanksgiving, it''s just my favorite. I can have Thanksgiving all year round.', 74349, 0), (472135, 'Agriculture is a business that has been up to its bib overalls in politics since the first Thanksgiving dinner kickback to the Indians for subsidizing Pilgrim maize production with fish head fertilizer grants.', 10731, 0), (472136, 'I started acting in second grade - my first role was in the Thanksgiving play. I was the Indian chasing the turkey. All the other mom''s encouraged my mom to get me into acting after that. Also, when I saw ''The Sound of Music'' at Music Circus, I knew I wanted to act.', 46525, 0), (472137, 'Thanksgiving is one of my favorite American traditions. I quickly picked it up when I moved to the U.S. from Sweden.', 32425, 0), (472138, 'Thanksgiving is probably my favorite holiday - it''s a day that''s American to the core and it''s a day that''s all about what and how we eat.', 32425, 0), (472139, 'There was a time, in the not so distant past, that if you didn''t have what you needed on Thanksgiving, you were pretty much going to have to wait until Friday. Not anymore!', 69132, 0), (472140, 'My mum, Helen, was hilarious. She had a tremendous sense of humour and was a great singer and tap dancer. For many years, she was the voice of Minnie Mouse in the Macy''s Thanksgiving Day Parade. She would be in the float as it came along, singing whatever the Minnie Mouse song of the day was. She was a really big spirit in my life.', 22849, 0), (472141, 'When I was about nine years old, I announced to my mother that I was going to cook Thanksgiving dinner. And I went to the library and got this whole pile of books. I''d love to say it all turned out great. It didn''t. But, sort of, from that point on, whenever there was serious cooking at home, I was the one who did it.', 10715, 0), (472142, 'As much as I love crisp, clean whites, there''s always a time for rich but balanced Chardonnays with oak, especially at Thanksgiving.', 11355, 0), (472143, 'I would love four children because I have a very small family, so I want those big Thanksgiving dinners.', 67832, 0), (472144, 'Lets talk about the holidays, more specifically, consumption during the holidays. If it''s true that ''We are what we eat,'' most of us would be unrecognizable during the period that ranges from the night before Thanksgiving through that day in early January when everyone decides to return to the gym.', 69076, 0), (472145, 'I always love the soapy conflicts between somebody''s family of origin and their new family - ''Do I have Thanksgiving at my husband''s parents'' house, or at my parents'' house?''', 69353, 0), (472146, 'We all have somebody that sits down at the Thanksgiving table and says the most outrageous things, and you''re doin'' the dishes with your sister, and you''re like, ''Omigod, can you believe she said that?''', 58173, 0), (472147, 'As a kid, I was always mad - just noticing the women at Thanksgiving, running around the kitchen, while the men were watching football. For one, I don''t want to cook, and for two, I hate football. I was stuck in the middle.', 28432, 0), (472148, 'Berries have a lot of soluble fiber. That''s why they gel up when you''re making your Thanksgiving cranberry sauce, with the pectin.', 69458, 0), (472149, 'I like to decide the night before Thanksgiving that I''m gonna do it, and I''ll see what riff raff is around. Then I get that last-minute surge of energy. But if I had two weeks to plan, sometimes I wish I wasn''t doing it. But very seldom does that happen.', 274, 0), (472150, 'On the morning of Thanksgiving, I would wake up to the home smelling of all good things, wafting upstairs to my room. I would set the table with the fancy silverware and china and hope that my parents and grandmother wouldn''t have the annual Thanksgiving fight about Richard Nixon.', 66987, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (472151, 'Thanksgiving is the only day of the year when most of the stores here are closed during the day and reopen after midnight. Even restaurants shut down for the holiday, except for the fast-food chains.', 68456, 0), (472152, 'If no one shopped on Thanksgiving Day, the stores wouldn''t open. End of story. I say we all take the pledge and stay home. Thanksgiving is a day to give thanks for what you have, not to save a few dollars to get more.', 37774, 0), (472153, 'I loved my mom so much because she had to work on a penny just to put food on the table... During the Depression in the United States, everybody had a tough time. And I was so hurt because she was crying that she didn''t have any food for us for Thanksgiving.', 65159, 0), (472154, 'A lot of Thanksgiving days have been ruined by not carving the turkey in the kitchen.', 14120, 0), (472155, 'When I was just starting out in the business, I used to love to watch Lorne Greene doing the Macy''s Thanksgiving Day Parade. I said right then, ''That''s what I want to do someday,'' and it''s been one dream that has come true.', 26513, 0), (472156, 'Throughout its history, the members of Shearith Israel have observed Thanksgiving by reciting in synagogue the same psalms of praise and gratitude sung by Jews all over the world on festive days like Hanukkah.', 70703, 0), (472157, 'I''ve always had fond memories of cooking Thanksgiving.', 69146, 0), (472158, 'My whole problem is that all of my favorite things at Thanksgiving are the starches, and everyone is trying to go low-carb this year, even a green vegetable has carbs in it.', 72720, 0), (472159, 'Not to sound too much like Christopher Guest in ''Waiting for Guffman,'' but on Thanksgiving you''re putting on a show!', 72720, 0), (472160, 'It wasn''t the traditional cooking most people do. For me, as a young chef, Thanksgiving meant going to work in the kitchen at places like Gotham, JoJo and Jean-Georges.', 69146, 0), (472161, 'I really don''t do much on the night of Thanksgiving other than bring the wine and carve the turkey. My contribution comes the day after, in the form of breakfast. I usually just forage through the leftovers for things that will go well with eggs.', 69146, 0), (472162, 'I love chicken. I would eat chicken fingers on Thanksgiving if it were socially acceptable.', 73216, 0), (472163, 'It''s so warm now, and Thanksgiving came so early - is it just me, or does it not really feel like Ramadan?', 17083, 0), (472164, 'Holiday binge-buying has deep roots in American culture: department stores have been associating turkey gluttony with its spending equivalent since they began sponsoring Thanksgiving Day parades in the early 20th century.', 69148, 0), (472165, 'Thanksgiving, our eminent moral holiday, doesn''t have much for children. At its heart are conversation, food, drink, and fellowship - all perks of adulthood.', 15862, 0), (472166, 'The craft Emmys are kind of the kids'' table at Thanksgiving. You''re not really invited to the big dance. It''s still really, really exciting, and the statue still counts.', 71158, 0), (472167, 'I''ve spent a lot of Thanksgivings on the road with my band, so anytime that I can spend Thanksgiving with my family in a traditional aspect, eating sweet potatoes and cranberries and stuffing and all the trappings of Thanksgiving and then get on a treadmill the next day extra long, I''m happy.', 69378, 0), (472168, 'North Carolina was where you could have Thanksgiving and feel like it was Thanksgiving.', 71252, 0), (472169, 'My son was born during my last semester in college. His due date was Thanksgiving, but he didn''t show up until finals week. I brought my books to the hospital and didn''t think anything of it. That is what a father is supposed to do.', 69154, 0), (472170, 'If you think about a Thanksgiving dinner, it''s really like making a large chicken.', 71677, 0), (472171, 'I absolutely adore Thanksgiving. It''s the 