eachers'' unions have done good work in this field, K through 12. Delaying first communions and bar mitzvahs until age 21 would be another positive step.', 10731, 0), (472612, 'There is a sense that things, if you keep positive and optimistic about what can be done, do work out.', 66567, 0), (472613, 'We don''t have enough support for maternal leave and the kinds of things that some of the European countries do. So we still make it hard on women to go into the work force and feel that they can be good at work but then doing the most important job, which is raising your children in a responsible and positive way.', 66567, 0), (472614, 'I would be delighted if the United States could have a positive relationship with Russia, and I would be thrilled if the Russian people, who are so capable, had a normal country that they could chart a different future.', 66567, 0), (472615, 'And we can see the positive impacts right here at Solyndra. Less than a year ago, we were standing on what was an empty lot. But through the Recovery Act, this company received a loan to expand its operations. This new factory is the result of those loans.', 1693, 0), (472616, 'Conservatism has had from its inception vigorously positive, intellectually rigorous agenda and thinking. That agenda should have in my three pillars: strengthen the economy, strengthen our security, and strengthen our families.', 52321, 0), (472617, 'I believe many people feel like God is mad at them. One day I put a post on Facebook that said, ''God is not mad at you.'' Within a few hours, we literally had thousands of positive responses from people saying things like, ''That is exactly what I needed to hear today.'' Obviously, this is a message we need to hear.', 1206, 0), (472618, 'Try to always stay focused on the objectives that are possible and the positive - and on having fun outside of the stuff that''s going on in Washington.', 17531, 0), (472619, 'I''m not afraid of having an agenda. I do have an agenda. It''s a positive agenda.', 17531, 0), (472620, 'Publishers like a good buzz, and negative responses sell books just as well as positive ones.', 1716, 0), (472621, 'We should be the pro-legal immigration party. A party that has a positive platform and agenda on how we can create a legal immigration system that works for immigrants and works for America.', 66707, 0), (472622, 'My mother was a very positive thinker; she was always active, always doing something good.', 4294, 0), (472623, 'I have never talked publicly or privately about the Jewish people, including conversations with President Nixon, except in the most positive terms.', 4008, 0), (472624, 'Good news doesn''t necessarily have to be a positive thing. Bringing good news is imparting hope to one''s fellow man.', 1883, 0), (472625, 'To be in any way a positive contribution, that''s all anybody wants to be. It''s all I''ve ever wanted to be. I wanted to be an artist, be a mother. You want to feel that in your life you''ve been of use, in whatever way that comes out.', 1380, 0), (472626, 'The Egyptian military plays positive and negative roles in Egypt, but the most significant single thing it did under Mubarak was to guarantee an Islamist victory once he left the scene.', 67439, 0), (472627, 'Is truth always positive? Of course. Once the truth comes out, you know, it''s all right. We''re scared that if the truth comes out that it''s not all right. It''s the other way around.', 1121, 0), (472628, 'When you go through a negative situation, don''t think about it. Make it positive.', 1121, 0), (472629, 'I''ve been singing for six years. I''ve been in and out of the studios with top producers, but it wasn''t something I was ready to express to the public or to the press. I wasn''t ready to come out. I wanted to perfect my voice and be 100 percent positive that I could come out right.', 1725, 0), (472630, 'I don''t want to use the term ''plus-size,'' because, to me, what the hell is that? It just doesn''t have a positive connotation to it. I tend to not use it.', 1725, 0), (472631, 'Enthusiasm is something so positive.', 67000, 0), (472632, 'Over time, if you want rights, you have to also show that you can use them responsibly and that you can build a positive world in the online space, and that''s also very important.', 17503, 0), (472633, 'Whether that''s positive or not, people are talking about the Old Vic Theater again with passion and commitment and controversy and debate.', 60302, 0), (472634, 'The people are rejecting so-called free trade and globalization that the elites presented as a positive thing.', 67839, 0), (472635, 'Because a person has to be either working or looking for work to be counted as part of the labor force, an increase in the number of people too discouraged to continue their search for work would reduce the unemployment rate, all else being equal - but not for a positive reason.', 66590, 0), (472636, 'I''m fundamentally a positive person. Otherwise, I wouldn''t be doing some of the insane movies that I do.', 68428, 0), (472637, 'There is only one thing for us to do, and that is to do our level best right where we are every day of our lives; To use our best judgment, and then to trust the rest to that Power which holds the forces of the universe in his hands.', 4025, 0), (472638, 'There are powers inside of you which, if you could discover and use, would make of you everything you ever dreamed or imagined you could become.', 4025, 0), (472639, 'I''ve had to deal with all different types of situations - positive and negative and extremes of both.', 66795, 0), (472640, 'I don''t even really know what it is I do for a living - the level of insecurity is very, very high. You''re making a lot of money, getting a lot of accolades and positive criticism for something where you don''t even know what you''re doing.', 66795, 0), (472641, 'I do expect a lot from myself, but it''s also a balance of being... positive and also pushing yourself.', 37889, 0), (472642, 'I''m part of the mushball middle. I consider ''confused'' the majority position because, thankfully, most people would rather be uncertain some of the time than 100% positive all the time - even when they''re wrong.', 11414, 0), (472643, 'I''m hoping that these next 20 years will show what we did 20 years ago in sequencing the first human genome, was the beginning of the health revolution that will have more positive impact in people''s lives than any other health event in history.', 68729, 0), (472644, 'I came into this environment where there was so much love, so much positive energy. I never heard my parents say, ''We have adopted kids.'' The minute my sister Linda and I landed in Sweden, we were their kids.', 32425, 0), (472645, 'Positive, adj.: Mistaken at the top of one''s voice.', 224, 0), (472646, 'This is our job as leaders: to offer positive solutions and empower people. Our duty is to tackle our problems before they tackle us.', 66572, 0), (472647, 'It comes down to building your own world out here on the road. It''s who you surround yourself with. My band and crew are really positive guys.', 34097, 0), (472648, 'In nicey-nicey land, you must be happy-clappy and positive all the time - bad news is taboo.', 10407, 0), (472649, 'Love is a positive effect. Love can never have a negative effect, only a positive effect.', 13964, 0), (472650, 'My father''s music gives hope to people and also inspires them to break the bonds of injustice and to be positive in life. I''ve seen that everywhere I go, especially in poor countries and poor neighborhoods.', 13964, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (472651, 'Getting elected Governor of New Mexico, I really did enjoy that job. I thought I made a really big difference, and I think the same running for president of the United States - that I could make a really big, positive difference.', 68241, 0), (472652, 'You''re much better off creating positive rewards, complimenting people for acting correctly, rather than punishing them when they act incorrectly.', 11321, 0), (472653, 'I try to stay positive and be very, very active.', 1245, 0), (472654, 'If you have a negative thought - ''I can''t stand my boss'' - it perpetuates a negative worldview. But if you supplant each negative thought with three positive ones, you begin to restructure your brain.', 1245, 0), (472655, 'There are a lot of perks that come with fame, and with every positive there''s a negative, and then it all kind of balances out.', 20099, 0), (472656, 'The positive news is that the British economy is continuing to grow and is creating jobs. And it is positive news too that at a time of real international instability we are a safe haven in the storm.', 70252, 0), (472657, 'Among many of my friends and acquaintances, I seem to be one of the very few individuals who felt or feels no ambivalence about my mother. All my feelings for my mother were positive, very strong and abiding.', 852, 0), (472658, 'It is questionless desirable in all ordinary cases, wherever positive law is established, to restrain ourselves within the letter of that law and to allow the criminal all the benefit, if benefit to him shall result, of any evasion or escape that the law shall afford him.', 20151, 0), (472659, 'We shot many films in Delhi that turned out to be successful at the box office. So the attachment is definitely on the positive side.', 66951, 0), (472660, 'All the evidence, experimental and even a little theoretical, seems to indicate that it is the energy content which is involved in gravitation, and therefore, since matter and antimatter both represent positive energies, gravitation makes no distinction.', 66888, 0), (472661, 'It''s much more powerful and compelling to create a positive vision than it is to tear somebody down.', 67775, 0), (472662, 'If we''re stuck with having expectations, there''s a very good reason to embrace positive ones: It''s that we often create what we anticipate.', 29471, 0), (472663, 'I''ve had a very positive experience in L.A. in the comedy world and found everyone to be very nice and welcoming. It''s been really fun.', 67541, 0), (472664, 'I love America. It''s such a positive country.', 67831, 0), (472665, 'For me to go to America - which I find such a positive place - well, I took to it like a duck to water.', 67831, 0), (472666, 'You know, I love America. It''s such a positive country.', 67831, 0), (472667, 'A positive frame of mind will definitely enhance your travelling experience. If I''m not in a positive frame of mind then the whole thing definitely becomes more of a challenge for me.', 67812, 0), (472668, 'I think the Internet is a huge positive.', 58696, 0), (472669, 'I don''t know if the term ''liberation theology,'' which can be interpreted in a very positive sense, will help us much. What''s important is the common rationality to which the church offers a fundamental contribution, and which must always help in the education of conscience, both for public and for private life.', 856, 0), (472670, 'Right now people seem to be very tentative about the positive benefits of capitalism.', 68245, 0), (472671, 'Don''t give up, be positive and if you know someone who knows someone at a record company don''t stop beating down their door till you get heard. Don''t ever say it''ll never happen or it''ll never happen.', 47442, 0), (472672, 'Prior to getting into music, I interacted with, on a daily basis, about 5-10 percent of the people that I''ve interacted with since then. I''ve been meeting people from different backgrounds and different cultures. That did allow for a lot of change. I''ve changed as a product of that, but it''s been positive.', 67010, 0), (472673, 'Positive market incentives operating in the public interest are too few and far between, and are also up against a seemingly never-ending expansion of perverse incentives and lobbying.', 67778, 0), (472674, 'To me, success is making a positive difference through art - making art that affects the world and that changes the way people feel about themselves and the world.', 69328, 0), (472675, 'I just want to make sure that I''m taking roles that are positive, real, honest reflections of African-Americans because I do think the media can put African-American women in the background. Then, unfortunately, what happens is, subconsciously, our culture begins to assess that as reality.', 69328, 0), (472676, 'It''s also a question of finding good material and interesting roles. I''m not the only actress out there, and good parts just don''t fall into your lap that easily. But I like most of the films I''ve made recently and so I''m pretty positive about the future.', 70658, 0), (472677, 'I should think wrestling is the most positive thing in the world. The fact is, behind the scenes, there''s stuff that goes on that''s bush-league. It''s laughable.', 67851, 0), (472678, 'I had creative control over my character, which means if they wanted me to do something that I didn''t agree with, then I wouldn''t do it. If it was good for the show, then I had no problem. If it was demeaning to the character and wasn''t adding a positive light to the show, then I can guarantee that I wouldn''t do it.', 67851, 0), (472679, 'A lot of our Democratic consultants have fallen into the self-defeating prescription that the candidate that runs the most negative ads wins. I have a new theory: Positive is the new negative.', 67011, 0), (472680, 'Those at the top would do better with a smaller share of a booming economy that elicits a positive politics than they will do with an ever-larger share of an anemic economy that fuels the politics of anger.', 66627, 0), (472681, 'There''s nothing that sells good about Allen Iverson if it''s something positive about Allen Iverson.', 67386, 0), (472682, 'I have nothing to lose and think that it''s a positive thing that I am young and playing on a good level.', 69728, 0), (472683, 'My mom was always the support. I can always go out to her and she''ll always find the positive in things.', 69728, 0), (472684, 'More brands are waking up to their social responsibility and doing good work through cause marketing campaigns. Yet too many still go about it the wrong way. I mean ''wrong'' in two senses. Firstly, they are marketing ineffectively, and secondly, as a consequence their positive social impact is not maximized.', 66797, 0), (472685, 'Monopolies are bad and deserve their reputation when things are static and the monopolies function as toll collectors... But I think they''re quite positive when they''re dynamic and do something new.', 30539, 0), (472686, 'We have initiated programs for re-entry offenders, since some 500,000 to 600,000 offenders will come out of prison each year for the next three or four years. We want to have positive alternatives when they come back to the community.', 65233, 0), (472687, 'You know, the standard state for people is ''mildly pleasant.'' Negative emotions are quite rare, and extremely positive emotions are rare. But people are mildly pleased most of the time, they''re mildly tired a lot of the time, and they wish they were somewhere else a substantial part of the time - but mostly they''re mildly pleased.', 6017, 0), (472688, 'It''s always a positive when radio is playing your music and fans are responding.', 69332, 0), (472689, 'That''s my gift. I let that negativity roll off me like water off a duck''s back. If it''s not positive, I didn''t hear it. If you can overcome that, fights are easy.', 26132, 0), (472690, 'STAR TREK is a show that had a vision about a future that was positive.', 45192, 0), (472691, 'At the core of ''Star Trek'' is Gene Roddenberry''s vision of the future. So much of science-fiction is about a dystopian society with human civilization having crumbled. He had an affirmative, shining, positive view of the future.', 45192, 0), (472692, 'That''s all I could ever hope for, to have a positive effect on women. ''Cos women are powerful, powerful beings. But they''re also the most doubtful beings. They''ll never know - we''ll never know - how powerful we are.', 7387, 0), (472693, 'I believe that you should gravitate to people who are doing productive and positive things with their lives.', 14526, 0), (472694, 'My goal is to make people feel passionately, if it''s negative or positive, I did my job.', 72053, 0), (472695, 'Even if you have some extra kilos, you don''t need to kill yourself for that; you just have to look at yourself as a positive.', 67736, 0), (472696, 'A President cannot always be popular.', 16121, 0), (472697, 'I''ve gotten nothing but warmth from the Black community and positive feedback.', 50400, 0), (472698, 'If you believe - which I do - that acting is a bit like advocacy for your character, then of course I want to find the positive points.', 67015, 0), (472699, 'I''m always fighting the cup-is-half-empty way of being, versus the cup-is-half-full. I''m always fighting the pessimistic versus the positive.', 25658, 0), (472700, 'The rapid growth of prenatal testing has had some undeniably positive effects: A woman who knows she will bear a child with a handicap can plan to deliver in a hospital equipped for risky births. And many couples prefer the opportunity to prepare psychologically for the work of raising a disabled child.', 70989, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (472701, 'I want to own a network. I want to own a network where you can turn it on with your family all day long and get positive reinforcement.', 1776, 0), (472702, 'Putting aside for the moment the question of whether human industrial CO2 emissions are having an effect on climate, it is quite clear that they are raising atmospheric CO2 levels. As a result, they are having a strong and markedly positive effect on plant growth worldwide. There is no doubt about this.', 69891, 0), (472703, 'I believe in the imperative to explore, so any project that I can be involved with that celebrates that, and expands people''s imagination around that idea of pushing out, is one of the most positive things that I think I could be involved with.', 69923, 0), (472704, 'Media images are so important to young people feeling positive about themselves.', 66644, 0), (472705, 'I do want to be involved in quality projects that say something positive about the Latino community.', 66644, 0), (472706, 'There just aren''t enough positive portrayals of Latino life in film.', 66644, 0), (472707, 'Now is the time for the U.S. and the nations of Western Europe who engaged in the slave trade throughout this hemisphere to come forward in a positive way to assist in undoing the harm that was caused by their past colonial policies in the hemisphere.', 41313, 0), (472708, 'As far as vanity and wrinkles and things like that, that''s a part of life I don''t worry about. I put on creams, you know, but don''t go mad, and I don''t have any kind of treatments. I just live a healthy lifestyle. And staying happy, not getting negative and angry, I think that helps, looking at the positive of everything.', 65023, 0), (472709, 'I want to encourage people. One of the things I do encourage people is that - that Internet is a place where we should share our ideas and be positive, not negative.', 69335, 0), (472710, '''The Fault in Our Stars'' is a beautiful film that''s really positive. The second half gets sad, but it''s always positive.', 69335, 0), (472711, 'Fan Luv is a powerful positive movement. All over the world they come. It''s a force of luv.', 68176, 0), (472712, 'There''s a positive side to film and television, the sense of feeding into the theater... Your fans will follow you, hopefully, and be open-minded to see you play other things and experience other stories you want to tell.', 51377, 0), (472713, 'There''s not always going to be something out there for you, especially not a positive role, so once you get up there and start being well known, you can''t just think projects will come to you. You have to start doing your own projects because if you don''t, you''ll miss out, and eventually your fame will be over.', 68249, 0), (472714, 'I always try to set a positive example for my generation and promote confidence.', 68249, 0), (472715, 'It''s human nature that if you get 20 positive comments and one negative one, you''re going to focus on the negative. We all do that. It can be something that drags you down. It''s easy to get bogged down with it, but I try to concentrate on the good things.', 68250, 0), (472716, 'Everybody can make a choice to be more positive. It''s about who you hang around and what you choose to watch on TV. What environment you put yourself in. It''s easy to get a negative internal dialogue. You have to be aware of what''s playing in your mind.', 58655, 0), (472717, 'In our family health, it''s about having a balanced life, about laughing and staying on a positive note.', 58655, 0), (472718, 'There will be a huge, huge positive impact for society when driverless cars become a thing.', 69679, 0), (472719, 'Even before you get to self-driving vehicles, there''s just a huge amount of positive things that happen to cities when you do ridesharing.', 69679, 0), (472720, 'The positive is I''m delighted at the way the Liberal Democrats as a party have supported me and the way in which the work I''m doing, through the Liberal Democrats, has abled to broaden some of the work I work on.', 10487, 0), (472721, 'My mom is positive and optimistic.', 68105, 0), (472722, 'Obviously social media has had a massive impact on the fame game, but not in a positive way. But it can be for some.', 68181, 0), (472723, 'When I was a kid, no one would believe anything positive that you could say about black people. That''s a terrible burden.', 19298, 0), (472724, 'What I have is P.H. positive chronic myeloid leukemia, which is an aberration in your white blood cells.', 19298, 0), (472725, 'I prefer a positive view of freedom, drawing on another tradition of political thinking that goes all the way back to the ancient Greek polis.', 67458, 0), (472726, 'Positive characterizations are complex characterizations. That''s all we need to know. They shouldn''t be saccharine. They shouldn''t feel like medicine.', 5054, 0), (472727, 'You know, often films that are deemed positive, nobody wants to see them.', 5054, 0), (472728, 'In Hollywood, there is one dominant voice. It is a white, male, straight gaze. When I talk about positive portrayals of black people and women, I''m saying complexity. I''m not saying goody-two-shoes, everything''s okay. No. The positive view of me is to see me as I am: the ''good,'' the ''bad,'' the gray. That is a positive portrayal.', 5054, 0), (472729, '''Yes'' is the mother of all positive words, next to ''love.'' Maybe ''love'' is the father of all positive words.', 397, 0), (472730, 'When I first ran, being a woman in politics was seen as both a negative and also a positive. You could attract more women voters, but on the other hand, a lot of men wouldn''t vote for you.', 70540, 0), (472731, 'I like my social media space to be somewhere very positive... I like to just be able to just share any images they see, or a piece of art or an item of clothing, and get to share that with the world.', 69238, 0), (472732, 'I think the best way to fight your detractors is to produce positive results and not think about them, but think about winning the hearts and minds of North Carolinians - or Americans - on good policy.', 68112, 0), (472733, 'A focus on regulatory overreach, things that the benefit doesn''t outweigh the cost, is probably the single greatest opportunity we have for having a positive impact on job creation.', 68112, 0), (472734, 'Early on, after gay liberation, there was an almost Stalinist pressure from gay critics and even gay readers to write about positive role models. We were never supposed to write negative things about gays, or else we were seen as collaborating with the enemy.', 9683, 0), (472735, 'Doing and making positive programming for young people is so important to me, and I will keep doing it.', 68211, 0), (472736, 'The proper governmental policy in a depression is strict laissez-faire, including stringent budget slashing, and coupled perhaps with positive encouragement for credit contraction.', 17756, 0), (472737, 'Contrary to popular mythology, the best and most durable relationships are based not on vulnerability or passion but on a conjugation of positive attributes, a meeting of mind, body and soul that is all the more powerful as it is not weighed down with neediness and unreasonable expectation.', 67020, 0), (472738, 'Translating any insights I have for strangers'' lives into positive action in my own has proved a challenge. While I''ve learned a lot about what everyone else is thinking, I fail miserably to use such knowledge in my private relationships.', 67020, 0), (472739, 'When did the word ''compromise'' get compromised? When did the negative connotations of ''He was caught in a compromising position'' or ''She compromised her ethics'' replace the positive connotations of ''They reached a compromise''?', 41330, 0), (472740, 'I have had positive experiences with cameras. When I have been asked to join experiments using cameras in the courtroom, I have participated; I have volunteered.', 11622, 0), (472741, 'If I write a book where all I''ve ever experienced is success, people won''t take a positive lesson from it. In being candid, I have to own up to my own failures, both in my marriage and in my work environment.', 11622, 0), (472742, 'If you look at the history of Wonder Woman, you look at the iconography, the images that have kept her alive - they''re not dark. The thing I think is so important to always keep in mind about her is how positive and bright and shiny she is - very much in the same way that Superman has been.', 68686, 0), (472743, 'Secretariat was just ridiculously endowed with every positive quality that a person would seek out in a non-human. He was very aware of his environment he surveyed the terrain before he ran and would look people in the eye. ', 67021, 0), (472744, 'But you see, our society is still trapped in this binary, black/white logic and that has had some very positive implications for our generation. It''s had some very negative ones as well and one of the negative ones is that it creates enormous identity problems for people who have one black ancestor and all white ancestors for example.', 66934, 0), (472745, 'So many of our young women today, they''re growing up without a father, but they''re still thirsty for that and desiring positive male love.', 68255, 0), (472746, 'Whenever there''s an opportunity to celebrate the written word and celebrate the folks that read the written word, and, I think, to encourage other writers to write and encourage folks to read more and get connected to it in a personal way, it''s a positive thing.', 68255, 0), (472747, 'Food has always brought me comfort and the bingeing is triggered when I''m in a space that is not positive.', 47095, 0), (472748, 'I try to be positive. I speak to my players about how we have to play, respect the rules. What I have done is always be positive.', 73172, 0), (472749, 'Everyone in L.A. is very positive and upbeat, whereas London can get quite miserable at times.', 67853, 0), (472750, 'I want to work with Peter Robinson as first minister in a positive, constructive way and leave the elections to the electorate.', 67683, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (472751, 'It is mistaken to claim that global problems will be solved more quickly if only researchers would abandon their quest to understand the universe and knuckle down to work on an agenda of public or political concerns. These are not ''either/or'' options - indeed, there is a positive symbiosis between them.', 67022, 0), (472752, 'A lasting solution to this problem will have an exceptionally positive influence foremost on the peoples of Palestine and Israel, as well as on the region and the international community.', 67741, 0), (472753, 'One reason why it has become harder to promote the beneficial side of emotions such as anger is that the moral vocabulary of good and bad has been replaced by the self-help lexicon of positive and negative thinking.', 67531, 0), (472754, 'Everybody thinks when I say a guy is a good game manager, that''s a negative, but I think it''s a real positive. You have the ball in your hand every time when you''re a quarterback. Whether you''re handing it off or throwing to somebody, I think that''s extremely important.', 68258, 0), (472755, 'I like to think of myself as a positive person. Otherwise I wouldn''t have had a child.', 66917, 0), (472756, 'My mother''s songs are really turning out to be masterpieces. I have inherited this incredible legacy and am so fortunate to bathe in her sensibilities. It is tinged with tragedy. I''d much rather she was here in person, but there is still a positive force to come out of her death and that is having the gift of music that she gave.', 8055, 0), (472757, 'However much some journalists may criticize me, I know that I look, feel, and behave several decades younger than my actual age, and much of that is because I believe you are what you think you are. This is called positive affirmation, and it''s a really strong tool.', 50885, 0), (472758, 'I think people are so immersed in the anti-Scientology mindset by consuming tabloid media and stories about space aliens. It''s baffling. When I say I want to see a more positive side of the church, all I''m saying is I want to get past these headlines that talk about aliens and Tom Cruise jumping on a sofa.', 70667, 0), (472759, 'I''m a big believer in the power of visualizations. And so are neuroscientists. Numerous studies have proven how merely imagining positive circumstances sends blood flowing from negative brain regions to positive ones.', 5238, 0), (472760, 'One tech-related concern with religion is that it appears to be a positive feedback loop to the accelerating rich-poor gap, as the disenfranchised opt out of modernity.', 68924, 0), (472761, 'I''m pretty positive, optimistic, so I always expect the best.', 69324, 0), (472762, 'I''m usually always very happy and funny and positive. It''s only when I''m tired that I get a little low energy.', 68008, 0), (472763, 'You need to train your brain to be positive.', 68008, 0), (472764, 'The best way to prevent the homegrown-inspired attacks is literally positive engagement with Muslim communities. Making sure that any immigrant population that comes into America assimilates, becomes part of our culture. That has been our history; it has made us strong.', 71239, 0), (472765, 'I''m a positive guy, even if I don''t smile a lot.', 67759, 0), (472766, 'Is detachment the answer to freedom? No, because detachment is negative - it is to be without. The answer must be positive - I must replace what I have with something better.', 9130, 0), (472767, 'I never want to record something that I''m not proud of just because I think it might be a big hit. There''s no positive about that because if you record a song you hate and it''s a big hit, then you''re singing a song every night that you hate. And if you record a song that you hate and it isn''t a hit, then you sold out for no reason.', 56, 0), (472768, 'Staying consistent with positive habits can be a challenge.', 66659, 0), (472769, '''MMMbop'' ultimately is about trying to see the positive in the negative, trying to see the positive relationships you''ll have the in the face of challenge and strife.', 69350, 0), (472770, 'I think, as athletes, we''ve been given a platform, and we can use it in a lot of different ways. We can use it for negative. We can use it for positive. We can be indifferent. But if you''ve been given a platform, I think God is pleased when you share... His truth in love.', 67856, 0), (472771, 'A core part of Teach For America''s mission has always been affecting positive change in the traditional public school system.', 67447, 0), (472772, 'You don''t have to be positive all the time.', 68264, 0), (472773, 'Talking about income inequality, even if you''re not on the Forbes 400 list, can make us feel uncomfortable. It feels less positive, less optimistic, to talk about how the pie is sliced than to think about how to make the pie bigger.', 52668, 0), (472774, 'The main point of democracy is to deliver positive results for the majority.', 52668, 0), (472775, 'Kids need role models, whether it''s baseball players, actors or musicians: people to bring a little positive light into their hearts and minds. We need to be a little kinder to those people because it''s not easy being that role model, looked upon as something we are all incapable of being - too perfect.', 70631, 0), (472776, 'Saudi Arabia isn''t the enemy, but it is a problem. It could make so much positive difference in the Islamic world if it used its status to soothe Sunni-Shiite tensions and encourage tolerance. For a time, under King Abdullah, it seemed that the country was trying to reform, but now under King Salman, it has stalled.', 47722, 0), (472777, 'I like to accept it all, the negative and the positive.', 68265, 0), (472778, 'Happiness is just a positive perception from our brain. Some days, you will be unhappy. Our brain is a tool we use. It''s not who we are.', 20595, 0), (472779, 'You are always, always overwhelmed by positive response because you know it can go either way.', 71241, 0), (472780, 'There''s not a lot of positive role models of women in newspapers and magazines. I think it puts pressure on girls. They think that the image put out, it''s the way you have to look.', 69734, 0), (472781, 'Atoms consist of a positive nucleus and negative electrons flying around outside it. Electrons closest to the nucleus feel a strong negative-on-positive tug, and the bigger atoms get, the bigger the tug. In really big atoms, electrons whip around at speeds close to the speed of light.', 13375, 0), (472782, 'I wasn''t a vegan when I came to Congress. It was a decision I made soon after I got here, and it''s had such a positive impact on my life that I decided to try to help others as well.', 71202, 0), (472783, 'Making great strides without a well-defined purpose will not bring positive results.', 53857, 0), (472784, 'I try to be as positive as I can because I truly believe I am my feelings, and if I''m sad, if I have regrets, they will show up as illnesses, they will show up as cancers... I don''t want that.', 72054, 0), (472785, 'When you''ve been touched by sadness and grief, it makes you vulnerable. And because I am vulnerable, I try to be positive. And when I say ''try,'' I really do mean try, because it''s an effort.', 72054, 0), (472786, 'If anybody has a bad day, they''ll just come to my room because they know I''ll bring out the positive in everything, or I''ll make them laugh, or I''ll be just crazy.', 72055, 0), (472787, 'Even when people don''t stay married, they can still be a family together. That''s been something that''s been really good for developing me as a person. It''s been a very positive learning experience.', 67858, 0), (472788, 'People are rejecting the power of the elite, but individuals such as Snowden are doing so in a positive way, trying to change things for the better. He is a very intelligent man and obviously interested in electronic music.', 66933, 0), (472789, 'I had no precise plan when I started ''Electronica,'' but I think it has been a very positive journey for me.', 66933, 0), (472790, 'I always welcome being part of something positive in WWE.', 13941, 0), (472791, 'Political folk talk a lot these days about ''messaging'' - a neologism designed to describe the way in which parties and politicians consciously characterize their efforts. It is only intended to be positive - i.e., ''Our messaging is designed to show we care.''', 68723, 0), (472792, 'It''s difficult to change things in a positive way.', 69737, 0), (472793, 'Senator Tester is wise enough to make sure his voice is heard in a positive manner to get things done.', 67835, 0), (472794, 'I think for any small business that''s bootstrapped, the overwhelming challenge initially is getting to positive cash flow.', 66656, 0), (472795, 'We Americans typically are more positive about our individual futures, which we have some control over, than we are the nation''s or the world''s, which we see largely through the media prism.', 73996, 0), (472796, 'Magic to me is you make a movie and it''s all great and it clicks, and at the end of the day you feel like you''re having an experience that is positive and that you''re learning from.', 64247, 0), (472797, 'My first instinct when I write songs is not a negative one. It''s something positive... Everything I''ve ever done has some form of hope in it, I think.', 13014, 0), (472798, 'My father... gave me a positive connection with men because he is a gentleman.', 67860, 0), (472799, 'I''ve struggled with depression before. For me, music was always a very positive way to will myself out of that situation.', 74384, 0), (472800, 'I believe all positive things and negative things are valuable because they shape you.', 66890, 0);
